messages.content: As an AI assistant, my role is to meticulously analyze criminal justice documents and extract information about law enforcement personnel. The response will contain: 1) The name of a law enforcement personnel. The individual's name must be prefixed with one of the following titles to be in law enforcement: Detective, Sergeant, Lieutenant, Captain, Deputy, Officer, Patrol Officer, Criminalist, Technician, Coroner, or Dr. Please prefix the name with 'Officer Name: '. I will derive this data from the following paragraph: Investigator Lew!s and Chauffer Rodney Robinson arrived at the scene at 12:31am to assess the situation. They promptly discovered the victim and called for Technician Muhammad to collect evidence. Muhammad arrived, snapping photos and gathering a spent casing, identified as a

9mm Luger. The nearby area was combed for additional clues by Sergeant McMullen, who briefed Detective Morton on the findings. Detective Morton then proceeded to oversee the collection of evidence by Crime Lab Technician Tamika Rogers, who conducted gunshot residue tests on the eyewitnesses, Darceleen Commodore and Earlitta Taylor. The Coroner's Office, represented by Dr. David Trehan, later declared the incident a double homicide. Detective Aucoin, after finding a set of keys, secured the crime scene, leaving it marked by the Orleans Parish Coroner's Office. Further investigation led Detective Morton to interview Darceleen Commodore, who identified one Kendall Gordon as an assailant, with a 90% certainty. Detective Pratt and Detective Mathews compiled photographic line-ups to aid the eyewitnesses' recollection. Officers Phil Burras & Quincy Broaden, Nate Addison & Glen Hewitt, and Detective Gregory Johnson, along with Detective Jason McGee and Detective Ananie Mitchell were dispatched to assist. Detective Melvin McCullum was later tasked with handling a related scene. The detailed work of Scientific Criminal Investigations Division Officer Gary Sallienger was crucial in documenting the scene. Detectives Venezia and Gebbia took over the interviews, with Sergeant Townsend managing the crime scene operations, and Sergeant Ruiz coordinating the investigative efforts.
Identify each individual in the transcript, by name, who are directly referred to as officers, sergeants, lieutenants, captains, detectives, homicide officers, and crime lab personnel.
